at the margin of an experimental plot in well­drained forest at Paracou. Felled by cuts through the buttresses about 1 m above the ground, this tree was the only roost of 
<taxonomicName id="00B03685FFB2FF81FF2E21E2FEE78D3E" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1867" box="[220,364,1008,1029]" class="Mammalia" family="Emballonuridae" genus="Peropteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="33" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucoptera">
